# Insect Wars — Project Overview

## What This Is

Insect Wars is a **real-time strategy (RTS) game** built in **Unity 6** (6000.x) using **URP** (Universal Render Pipeline). The game is set at **insect scale** — a patch of garden soil where pebbles are mountains, grass blades are trees, and dewdrops are lakes. Players command insect colonies (workers, fighters, ranged bombardiers) to gather resources, build structures, and destroy the enemy hive.

**Current state:** Single-player skirmish demo with AI opponent. No multiplayer/networking. Three scenes: `Home` (menu), `Game` (production gameplay — loads any map via `SkirmishMapDefinition` data), and `SkirmishDemo` (dev-only test scene, will be removed).

## Folder Structure

```
Assets/
  _InsectWars/          ← PRIMARY game content (all gameplay lives here)
    Scripts/
      Core/             ← Session, audio, scene loading, input, fonts
      Data/             ← ScriptableObject definitions (units, maps, visuals, terrain)
      RTS/              ← All gameplay systems (~40 scripts): units, buildings, AI, 
                          selection, commands, camera, fog, minimap, economy, combat, HUD
      RTS/Editor/       ← Custom inspectors
      UI/               ← Menu bootstrap
    Scenes/             ← Home.unity, Game.unity, SkirmishDemo.unity (dev-only)
    Models/             ← GLB-backed prefabs
    Materials/
    Sprites/            ← UI and VFX sprites
    Data/               ← ScriptableObject asset instances
    Editor/             ← Editor utilities and tests
  Settings/             ← URP pipeline assets, volume profiles
  Plans/                ← Design docs (markdown)
Packages/               ← manifest.json, embedded packages
ProjectSettings/        ← Unity project config
```

## Key Technologies

- **Unity 6** with **Universal Render Pipeline (URP)**
- **New Input System** (`Mouse.current`, `Keyboard.current` — direct polling, not action-mapped)
- **AI Navigation** (NavMesh) for unit pathfinding
- No networking libraries; single-player only
- No assembly definitions for game code (uses default assembly)

## Single Resource Economy

There is only **one resource: Calories**. Workers gather from `RottingFruitNode` and deposit at the hive or nests.

## Two Teams Only

`Team.Player` and `Team.Enemy` (plus `Team.Neutral`). No multiple playable races or tech trees. Flavor distinction is cosmetic (naming and art).
